Moving into an apartment in manhatten (New York City for you country bumpkins =p) with my girlfriend, and obviously it being a NYC apartment, i have very limited space. Im trying to consolidate in terms of wires, and im wondering if a wireless router would be worth it? Just run the DSL into the router, prop it up on a wall, and let it supply my computer and my gf's laptop with an endless barrage of free porn.. err.. wonderful internet?<br>
<br>
Anyway seriously thoguh, the primary factors i am concerned about is taking a performance hit, im on a 2.53ghz Alienware p4 1gb ram etc etc and i hit like 600k dl's from high quality low traffic servers, (dl'ing updates from microsoft for example) and im worried about performance being hampered by the lack of wires. (somethings got to give) . Also, reliability? Will cell phones/radios etc interfere? Im living in a building with hundreds of other tenants who are likely to have all that crap going , and i just want to make sure im not gonna get Fubar internet. Im not worried about &quot;networking&quot; the computers, just basically sharing internet with the most possible efficiency.<br>
<br>
Anyone have a good model wireless router?<br>
A good model wired router if worst comes to worse? Currently looking at the Nexland SOHO - heard that was top for performance/reliability/options.<br>
<br>
Any info will be appreciated , i know my stuff in regards to computers, but this is uncharted waters for me. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=289373  target="web">Reksarl Chaoticfury</a><BR>
