<br>
If 2 Antenna's are closer than 5' to each other they usually cause signal loss every now and then.  Moving them farther apart did help.<br>
<br>
Your neighbor is using a Cordless phone and is on the phone durning the 5%.  Those do play havoc with wireless routers.<br>
<br>
Someone is also using a wireless network within 500' of you.  Even though there are channelization and 128WEP Keys they do intefere with each other.<br>
